      "status": "pending_image_audit"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 22,
      "text": "Tele. Room",
      "status": "pending_image_audit"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 23,
      "text": "Holloman",
      "status": "pending_image_audit"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 24,
      "text": "Gandy",
      "status": "pending_image_audit"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 25,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 26,
      "text": "The following information was obtained by Liaison",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 27,
      "text": "Supervisor M.W. Kuhrts at the Intelligence Advisory Committee - Watch",
      "status": "pending_image_audit"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 28,
      "text": "Committee special meeting on September 21, 1957, relative to the",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 29,
      "text": "captioned matter. The initial report in this matter was given by the",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 30,
      "text": "U.S. Air Defense Command to the White House on September 20, 1957,",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 31,
      "text": "reflecting that an unidentified flying object was picked up by radar",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 32,
      "text": "station at Montauk Point, Long Island, New York, at approximately",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 33,
      "text": "4 p.m., proceeding in a westward direction with an altitude of",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 34,
      "text": "50,000 feet and a speed of 2,000 knots (approximately 2300 miles per",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 35,
      "text": "hour). The radar station at Montauk Point maintained an image for",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 36,
      "text": "approximately one minute, and thereafter it was picked up by a radar",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 37,
      "text": "station at Benton, Pennsylvania (Wilkes-Barre, Pennsylvania), which",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 38,
      "text": "coincided with the Montauk Point pickup and was tracked by Benton for",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 39,
      "text": "approximately 9 minutes. Thereafter, jamming was reported by several",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 40,
      "text": "radar stations westward as far as Chicago.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 41,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 42,
      "text": "The Watch Committee at its meeting on September 21 was told",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 43,
      "text": "by the Air Defense Command that the original reports had been down-",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 44,
      "text": "graded, since there was an 11-minute break in the tracking by the",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 45,
      "text": "various radar stations, and further that weather conditions in the",
      "status": "pending_image_audit"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 46,
      "text": "area were of the type which have in the past produced false radar",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 47,
      "text": "\"pips\" and electronic information. Also, there were a number of",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 48,
      "text": "Strategic Air Command planes in the Chicago area on a training flight.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 49,
      "text": "The Watch Committee was told that the Air Defense Command has not",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 50,
      "text": "completed its investigation of this incident; however, in any event",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 51,
      "text": "it was reported that the phenomena reported west of Buffalo, New York,",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 52,
      "text": "were not related to the object as reported by Montauk Point and",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 53,
      "text": "Benton, Pennsylvania.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 54,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 55,
      "text": "The Watch Committee concluded that, \"It is highly improbable",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 56,
      "text": "that a Soviet operation is responsible for the unidentified flying",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 57,
      "text": "object reports of September, 1957.\" The Watch Committee in considering",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 58,
      "text": "this matter also concluded that there is no intelligence on Soviet",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 59,
      "text": "activities which can be related to a missile launching of this type.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 60,
      "status": "blank"
    },
